steps.instruction:
For a more step by step guide go [here](https://www.kingarthurflour.com/blog/2016/11/01/apple-pie-bakealong)

### Making the Crust
1. In a medium bowl whisk together 2.5 cups of all-purpose flour and 3/4 teaspoon of salt
2. Work in the shortening until the mixture is evenly crumbly 
3. Dice the butter into 1/2" pieces, and cut into the mixture until you have flakes of butter the size of a dime
4. At 2 tablespoons at a time add the 7 tablespoons of ice water **while** mixing with a fork
5. When the dough is moist enough to hold together when you squeeze it, transfer it to a piece of wax or parchment paper 
    - It's OK if there are some dry spots in the pile. Use a spray bottle of water to lightly spritz these places; that way you'll add just enough water to bring the dough together without creating a wet spot
6. Fold the dough over on itself three or four times to bring it together
7. Then divide it into two pieces, one about twice as large as the other 
8. The larger piece will be the bottom crust; the smaller piece will be the top crust 
9. Pat each piece of dough into a disk about 3/4" thick
10. Roll each disk on its edge, like a wheel, to smooth out the edges
    - This step will ensure your dough will roll out evenly, without a lot of cracks and splits at the edges later
11. Wrap in plastic and refrigerate for 30 minutes before rolling
12. Preheat the oven to 425F
13. Lightly grease a 9" pie pan that's at least 2" deep
    - This will make serving the pie easier after it's baked


### Making the Filling 
1. Peel and slice the apples 
2. Combine the sliced apples and lemon juice into a large bowl 
3. In a small bowl combine the sugar, 2 tablespoons of flour, cornstarch, 1/4 teaspoon of salt, and spices 
4. Sprinkle mixture over apples 
5. Stir to coat them 
6. Stir in the apple juice concentrate and the vanilla 


### Assembly 
1. Poll the larger piece of pastry into a 13" circle 
2. Transfer to the prepared pan 
3. Trim the edges so they overlap the rim of the pan by an inch all the way around 
4. Spoon the apple filling into the pan
    -- ***DO NOT*** top with the butter
5. Roll out the remaining dough to an 11" circle 
6. Carefully place the pastry on top of the apples
7. Pinch to seal the two and making a decorative crimp
8. Prick the crust with a fork or cut a decorative vent hole
8. Brush the top of the crust with milk (or an egg white beaten with 1 tablespoon of water) and sprinkle with coarse sugar
10. Place the pie in the fridge for 10 minutes
11. Place the pie on a parchment-lined baking sheet 
12. Bake at 425F for 20 minutes
13. Reduce temp to 375F and bake for 40 minutes 
    - Check the pie 10 min into the 40 minute bake and cover the edges with foil if its browning too quickly
14. Remove from oven 
15. Let it cool completely (lightly covered at room temp for several days, freeze if you need too)


#### Tips
- For a simple sugar-crumb crust in place of a pastry top crust, work together 1/2 cup each sugar, unbleached all-purpose flour, and butter (8 tablespoons), plus a pinch of salt, until sandy textured. Sprinkle atop the pie in place of the top crust; save the remaining top-crust pastry for another single-crust pie
